                            <comment id="15217931" author="lukasvasek" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 13:03:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok problem is following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JaxWsDynamicClientFactory.createClient creates new ClassLoader.&lt;br/&gt;
But this ClassLoader is never closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simple solution which worked for me should be to add to destroy() method &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ClassLoader cl = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();&lt;br/&gt;
ClassLoader parent = cl.getParent();&lt;br/&gt;
Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(parent);&lt;br/&gt;
cl = null;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a good solution could be to implement Autocloseable and inside it call destroy() to be backward compatible.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
